The paper deals with fine-grained sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The use of neural networks, specifically bidirectional LSTM and attention mechanism, suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The incorporation of CRF model for modeling dependencies among output labels indicates that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the use of Tripadvisor.com dataset and focus on opinion expression extraction suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
